      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "With just a broom and garbage bags, Gwynn spent 10 hours cleaning up the garbage, glass and debris that littered his neighborhood starting at 2 a.m., and when a group of neighbors had arrived later that morning to do the same job, Gwynn had already done most of the work! Eventually, his story was picked up by WKBW in Buffalo, and that's when another local citizen, Matt Block, got involved.",
